Quiz 43 Lightmaps

1. What is the effect of increasing the Auto UV Max Distance

- More charts are merged if the Auto UV Max Angle permits

2. What process should you use for designing the lighting in a scene if you intend to use Baked GI in th finished product?

- Start by using Precomputed Realtime GI then switch when you're happy

3. What effect does decreasing the Auto UV Max Angle have?

- Increases the number of charts if any were merged

4. Which preview textures will be displayed if we are only using Precomputed Realtime GI?

- Charting, Albedo, Emissive, Realtime Intensity, Realtime Direction

5. Which of the following options would allow you to visualise the UV unwrap of a lightmap?

- UV Charts